definitions.definition: Human skin tone, especially as an indicator of race or ethnicity.
definitions.example: Color has been a sensitive issue in many societies.

definitions.definition: Skin color, noted as normal, jaundiced, cyanotic, flush, mottled, pale, or ashen as part of the skin signs assessment.
A flushed appearance of blood in the face; redness of complexion.
Richness of expression; detail or flavour that is likely to generate interest or enjoyment.
definitions.example: Could you give me some color with regards to which products made up the mix of revenue for this quarter?

definitions.definition: A standard, flag, or insignia:
(in the plural) An award for sporting achievement, particularly within a school or university.
definitions.example: He was awarded colors for his football.

definitions.definition: (in the plural) The morning ceremony of raising the flag.
A property of quarks, with three values called red, green, and blue, which they can exchange by passing gluons.

A third-order measure of derivative price sensitivity, expressed as the rate of change of gamma with respect to time, or equivalently the rate of change of charm with respect to changes in the underlying asset price.
The relative lightness or darkness of a mass of written or printed text on a page. (See type color.)
Any of the colored balls excluding the reds.
A front or facade; an ostensible truth actually false; pretext.
An appearance of right or authority; color of law.
definitions.example: Under color of law, he managed to bilk taxpayers of millions of dollars.

definitions.definition: To give something color.
definitions.example: We could color the walls red.

definitions.definition: To apply colors to the areas within the boundaries of a line drawing using colored markers or crayons.
definitions.example: My kindergartener loves to color.

definitions.definition: (of a person or their face) To become red through increased blood flow.
definitions.example: Her face colored as she realized her mistake.

definitions.definition: To affect without completely changing.
definitions.example: That interpretation certainly colors my perception of the book.

definitions.definition: To attribute a quality to; to portray (as).
definitions.example: Color me confused.

definitions.definition: To assign colors to the vertices of a graph (or the regions of a map) so that no two vertices connected by an edge (regions sharing a border) have the same color.
definitions.example: Can this graph be 2-colored?

definitions.definition: Conveying color, as opposed to shades of gray.
definitions.example: Color television and movies were considered a great improvement over black and white.

definitions.definition: A person or a company that vends or sells.
A vending machine.
To bundle third-party dependencies with the source code for one's own program.
definitions.example: I distributed my application with a vendored copy of Perl so that it wouldn't use the system copies of Perl where it is installed.

definitions.definition: As the software vendor, to bundle one's own, possibly modified version of dependencies with a standard program.
definitions.example: Strawberry Perl contains vendored copies of some CPAN modules, designed to allow them to run on Windows.

definitions.definition: As it was in the beginning.
definitions.example: Originally, this paper was white, but over the years it has yellowed with age.

definitions.definition: In an original manner.
definitions.example: They had to think originally to come up with those creative ideas.

definitions.definition: Intelligence (secret information)
definitions.example: Intel is important in espionage.

definitions.definition: The state or condition of being useful; usefulness.
Something that is useful.
The ability of a commodity to satisfy needs or wants; the satisfaction experienced by the consumer of that commodity.
Well-being, satisfaction, pleasure, or happiness.
A service provider, such as an electric company or water company; or, the securities of such a provider.
A software program designed to perform a single task or a small range of tasks, often to help manage and tune computer hardware, an operating system or application software.
definitions.example: I've bought a new disk utility that can recover deleted files.

definitions.definition: The ability to play multiple positions.
The love of wisdom.
An academic discipline that seeks truth through reasoning rather than empiricism.
definitions.example: Philosophy is often divided into five major branches: logic, metaphysics, epistemology, ethics and aesthetics.

definitions.definition: A comprehensive system of belief.
A view or outlook regarding fundamental principles underlying some domain.
definitions.example: a philosophy of government;   a philosophy of education

definitions.definition: A general principle (usually moral).
A broader branch of (non-applied) science.
A calm and thoughtful demeanor; calmness of temper.
The size of type between long primer and pica, standardized as 11 point.
To philosophize.
